# GIT WORKFLOW

## Branch Strategy (Tree)

User visualizes with `git log --graph --all --oneline` or git GUI extensions.

```
ideate/{{TAG}}                 ← main branch (best version)
├── ideate/{{TAG}}/A           ← direction A
│   ├── ideate/{{TAG}}/A.1    ← sub-refinement
│   └── ideate/{{TAG}}/A.2    ← another sub-refinement
├── ideate/{{TAG}}/B           ← direction B
└── ideate/{{TAG}}/C           ← direction C
```

## Commit Conventions

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <what and why>`

| Type | Example |
|------|---------|
| `seed` | `seed: hierarchical sim2real for bimanual manipulation` |
| `survey` | `survey: found 15 papers on sim2real, 3 highly relevant` |
| `validate` | `validate(A): novel ⬤⬤⬤⬤○, feasible ⬤⬤⬤○○` |
| `direction` | `direction(A.1): add task-level domain randomization` |
| `decide` | `decide: pursue A.1, park B (too expensive)` |
| `dead-end` | `dead-end(A.2): per-joint DR infeasible — needs 8x A100` |
| `refs` | `refs: added 5 papers on domain randomization` |
| `converge` | `converge: final proposal — task-level DR + real finetuning` |
| `checkpoint` | `checkpoint: before pivoting from A to B` |

## Version Control Operations

```bash
# Explore a new direction
git checkout ideate/{{TAG}}
git checkout -b ideate/{{TAG}}/<dir_id>

# After direction is evaluated
git add doc/agent/ refs.db && git commit -m "validate(<dir_id>): <verdict>"

# If promising → merge back
git checkout ideate/{{TAG}} && git merge ideate/{{TAG}}/<dir_id>

# If dead end → leave branch, go back
git checkout ideate/{{TAG}}

# Checkpoint before risky decision
git add -A && git commit -m "checkpoint: before <decision>"
```

## Merging Two Directions

```bash
git checkout ideate/{{TAG}}
git checkout -b ideate/{{TAG}}/<merged_id>
# Write merged idea, validate, commit
```

