# REFERENCE DATABASE

All papers stored in `refs.db` (SQLite + FTS5). **Never use markdown tables for paper tracking.**

```bash
# Add a paper
python3 scripts/refs.py add --title "..." --arxiv "..." --direction seed --relevance high --notes "..."

# Search (full-text across title, abstract, notes)
python3 scripts/refs.py search "diffusion policy 3D"

# Get full details for one paper
python3 scripts/refs.py get ze2025improved

# Update after reading
python3 scripts/refs.py update ze2025improved --read --append-notes "Key insight: ..."

# Link paper to idea version
python3 scripts/refs.py link A.1 ze2025improved builds_on --note "Core method"

# List papers for a direction
python3 scripts/refs.py list --direction A.1 --relevance high

# Export
python3 scripts/refs.py export-bib > references.bib
python3 scripts/refs.py export-md > references.md
```

